'''十字包'''（{{lang-en|Hot cross bun}}）是一种添加了[[香料|香料]]的甜味的面包，面包中有[[黑加倫子|黑加倫子]]或[[葡萄干|葡萄干]]，面包上面有一个十字形符号。很多地区都有在[[耶稣受难日|耶稣受难日]]吃这种面包的传统，比如[[英国|英国]]、[[爱尔兰|爱尔兰]]、[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]]、[[新西兰|新西兰]]、[[加勒比海|加勒比海]]、[[南非|南非]]、[[印度|印度]]和[[加拿大|加拿大]]。但是现在有些地方全年可以买得到这种面包<ref name="news.bbc.co.uk">{{cite web |last=Rohrer |first=Finlo |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/8598312.stm |title=BBC - How did hot cross buns become two a penny? |publisher=BBC News |date=1 April 2010 |accessdate=26 April 2014 |archive-date=2018-06-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180613213448/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/8598312.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在澳洲，热十字包一般早在新年或[[圣诞节|圣诞节]]之后就开始出售了<ref>{{cite web |publisher = au.tv.yahoo.com |url = http://au.tv.yahoo.com/sunrise/soapbox/article/-/12491864/hot-cross-buns-on-sale-already-is-this-wrong/ |title = Hot Cross Buns on sale already |date = 4 January 2012 |accessdate = 28 December 2013 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141016032108/https://au.tv.yahoo.com/sunrise/soapbox/article/-/12491864/hot-cross-buns-on-sale-already-is-this-wrong/ |archivedate = 2014年10月16日 }}</ref><ref name=chron-xmas>{{cite news |last = Dodd |first = Kate |url = http://www.thechronicle.com.au/news/were-only-just-getting-over-christmas-and-new-year/2130077/ |title = Easter's come early: hot cross buns already on shelves |work = The Toowoomba Chronicle |date = 3 January 2014 |accessdate = 30 April 2014 |archive-date = 2015-06-01 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150601052915/http://www.thechronicle.com.au/news/were-only-just-getting-over-christmas-and-new-year/2130077/ |dead-url = no }}</ref>。

==历史==
在许多传统的基督教国家，从[[忏悔星期二|忏悔星期二]]的傍晚（[[圣灰星期三|圣灰星期三]]之前）到[[耶稣受难日|耶稣受难日]]的中午，人们一般会食用不含乳制品的小面包（大斋节期间禁食乳制品直到棕榈周日），通常是趁热或刚烤好的时候吃。<ref name=hutton>{{cite book |title = The Stations of the Sun: A History of the Ritual Year in Britain |url = https://archive.org/details/stationsofsunhis0000hutt_w2i1 |author=Ronald Hutton |page = [https://archive.org/details/stationsofsunhis0000hutt_w2i1/page/193 193] |isbn = 9-7801-92854-483 |publisher=Oxford University Press| year=2001}}</ref>

[[古希腊|古希腊]]人可能曾经在蛋糕上做十字形记号。

在伊丽莎白一世治下的英格兰，1592年，伦敦市场官员颁布了一项法令，禁止销售热十字包及其他含香料的面包，除了个别场合，如葬礼、[[耶稣受难日|耶稣受难日]]或[[圣诞节|圣诞节]]。违反此项法令的惩罚是没收所有违禁食品，并送给穷人。由于这项法令，那段时期热十字包主要在家庭厨房制作。在那之后，詹姆斯一世的英格兰和詹姆斯六世的苏格兰（1603-1625）也曾试图禁止这类面包的销售。<ref>{{cite news |url = http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9806E3D7133AE633A25752C3A9659C946396D6CF |work = The New York Times |title = Who Were The First To Cry "Hot Cross Buns?" |date = 31 March 1912 |accessdate = 4 May 2010 |archive-date = 2015-02-14 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150214122233/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9806E3D7133AE633A25752C3A9659C946396D6CF |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last = David |first = Elizabeth |authorlink1 = Elizabeth David |title = English Bread and Yeast Cookery |url = https://archive.org/details/englishbreadyeas00davi | chapter = Yeast Buns and Small Tea Cakes |publisher = The Viking Press |year = 1980 |location = New York |pages = [https://archive.org/details/englishbreadyeas00davi/page/473 473]–474 | accessdate = 2012-04-11 | isbn = 0670296538}}</ref>

==迷信说法==
英国民间传说有许多关于热十字包的迷信说法。其中一种说法是在[[耶稣受难日|耶稣受难日]]当天烘培并供应的面包在接下来那一整年都不会变质。还有传言劝人们留一块面包，因为生病的人要是吃一块面包病情就会好转。<ref name="practically">{{cite web |url = http://www.practicallyedible.com/edible.nsf/pages/hotcrossbuns |title = Hot Cross Buns |accessdate = 9 March 2009 |work = Practically Edible: The Web's Biggest Food Encyclopedia |publisher = Practically Edible |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090403185509/http://www.practicallyedible.com/edible.nsf/pages/hotcrossbuns |archivedate = 2009年4月3日 }}</ref>

1884年，夏威夷一份报纸刊登了一个广告，将在耶稣受难日销售热十字包。

传说与他人分享热十字包可以保证下一年友情不变。那时常说“给你一半给我一半，我们俩个友情不变”，因此还有说法是一次只能烤一个面包。还有人说因为面包上有个十字，吃之前要吻一下那个十字。如果带着热十字包出海还可以防止海难发生。挂一个热十字包在厨房，家里就不会发生火灾，并且保证烤出来的面包都很棒。挂着的包一年换一次。

== 其他版本 ==
英国的主要超市都制作与传统口味略微不同的热十字包，如[[太妃糖|太妃]]口味、橙汁[[蔓越莓|蔓越莓]]口味以及苹果[[肉桂|肉桂]]口味。

在澳大利亚和新西兰，有一种巧克力口味的包很受欢迎，在某些澳洲的面包店也销售咖啡口味的包<ref>{{cite web |url = http://jeanniebayb.livejournal.com/90073.html |title = Easter Baking: Hot Cross Buns |date = 24 March 2008 |website = jeanniebayb.livejournal.com |accessdate = 26 March 2008 |archive-date = 2010-04-05 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100405042353/http://jeanniebayb.livejournal.com/90073.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>。含有的香料都一样，只不过面包里添加的是巧克力碎而非黑加倫子。还有不含水果的、枣味的及焦糖口味的版本，以及巧克力口味和传统口味的迷你版面包<ref Name=woolies-versions>{{cite web |title=Yummy Hot Cross Buns |url=http://www2.woolworthsonline.com.au/Shop/Seasonal/Easter-Hot-Cross-Buns |accessdate=30 April 2014 |publisher=Woolworths (Australia) |archive-date=2015-04-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402110908/http://www2.woolworthsonline.com.au/Shop/Seasonal/Easter-Hot-Cross-Buns |dead-url=no }}</ref> 。

[[捷克|捷克]]有一种类似的蛋糕/甜面包，在复活节食用，面包上也标着一个十字，叫“mazanec”<ref>{{cite web |url=http://festivals.iloveindia.com/easter/traditions/easter-in-czech-republic.html |title=Easter in Czech Republic |accessdate=7 December 2007 |publisher=iloveindia.com |archive-date=2015-04-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402115554/http://festivals.iloveindia.com/easter/traditions/easter-in-czech-republic.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 十字符号 ==
过去，面包上的十字是由油酥糕粉制成<ref>{{cite book |last = Berry | first = Mary | authorlink = Mary Berry (food writer) | title = Mary Berry's Complete Cookbook | publisher = Dorling Kindersley |edition = First edition (2nd reprint) | year = 1996 | location = Godalming, Surrey | page = 386 | language = |ISBN = 1858335671 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last = Smith | first = Delia | authorlink = Delia Smith | title = Delia Smith's Cookery Course | publisher = British Broadcasting Corporation | edition = First edition (8th reprint) | year = 1986 | location = London | page = 62 | language = |ISBN = 0563162619 }}</ref>。现在一般是用普通面糊，也就是面粉加水<ref>{{Cite journal |title = The Great British Bake-off: Paul Holywood's Hot Cross Bun |journal = Easy Cook (magazine) | page = 38 | date = April 2013 | issue = 60}}</ref>。

